<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no" ?>
<FinalDraft DocumentType="Script" Template="No" Version="2">

  <Content>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Right" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="5.50" RightIndent="7.10" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Transition">
      <Text>FADE IN:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 5/8" Page="1" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRODY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JUDITH"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. LIVING ROOM - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The living room of an ordinary house in an ordinary road.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Despite the room being empty, the television has been left on. It is tuned to the Great British Shopping Experience, a shopping channel. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>On the television: Dan BRODY (slick, handsome, camp) is going through his sales patter.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Brody (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(singing)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">Hark the herald angels sing / Body bags are just the thing! / If your children are all dead / Don’t just leave them in their bed / If you want them up in Heaven / You must buy at least eleven / If their flesh has gone to Hell / A body bag will stem the smell/ Hark the herald angels sing/ Body bags are just the thing!  </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(talking)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes, folks! The hot, hot news here on the Great British Shopping Channel is that we’ve just got our sweaty mitts on a brand new batch of body bags! And these aren’t just any body bags, you know. Oh no. These are Chinese body bags made especially for the People’s Liberation Army in readiness for World War </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">III</Text>
      <Text>!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now you may remember the last time we had these on sale we sold out all five thousand within an hour and had to disappoint a lot of people. Were you one of those sad unfortunates? If so, what are you waiting for? Get on that phone right now and grab yourself a bargain!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’ve seen similar body bags on </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">eBay</Text>
      <Text> and said to yourself, ‘How much? Somebody’s having a laugh!’ And too bleeding right they are. In a moment of madness, Sam, our chief electrician here, bought one and has been laid up in bed for three days with buyers remorse!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And I don’t blame him! I saw the body bag he bought and I tell you this - I wouldn’t be seen dead in it!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>So don’t be a Sam! Save your money and get the real deal for a whole lot less right here, right now on the Great British Shopping Experience, the only shopping channel that doesn’t rip you off!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Unlike those nasty </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">knock-offs</Text>
      <Text> on </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">eBay</Text>
      <Text>, our body bags are fully waterproof, so no embarrassing leakages. They’re coated in insect-repellent, which will keep those filthy house flies at bay. I mean, who wants to see their loved ones turned into maggot meat? </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Yuk</Text>
      <Text>!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And look how tough this material is. Any stray dog thinking they’re going to make a meal of your </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">nana</Text>
      <Text> is in for a major disappointment. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Can body bags fly? You bet they can! Straight out that door and onto your doorstep in next to no time!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>But seemingly not just yet. A voice in my ear - a.k.a. Madame La Producer, a.k.a. She Who Must Be Obeyed - is telling me it's time for beddy-byes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>CAMERA tracks to the doorway and out into --</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="2" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="2" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRODY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. HALLWAY - NIGHT - CONTINUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BRODY (O.S.)(ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The Black Knight cometh, its wicked ways to perform, and so we have to leave it there for now. Please don't bother phoning. All the lines are now closed until the Black Knight has passed by once more. But worry ye not. We’ll be opening them again the moment it's safe to do so.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>CAMERA tracks up the stairs into -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="3" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="3" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRODY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. bedrOOM - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BRODY (O.S.)(ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>So this is me, Dan Brody, saying toodle-pip and may I on behalf of everyone here at the Great British Shopping Experience wish you and your loved ones a safe transition?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Bye, folks. See you tomorrow.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>TOM Caxton (in a red track suit) is tying up his wife, BARBARA (in a blue track suit).</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Kneeling on the bed, Barbara is completely compliant as Tom skillfully binds her. Next to her on the bed is a book on </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Shibari</Text>
      <Text>, the Japanese art of knot tying.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>When he is done tying up Barbara, Tom checks the ropes and knots. Then he helps Barbara get comfortable and pulls the bedclothes over her before kissing her tenderly on the forehead.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>They exchange anxious looks, offer each other re-assuring smiles. Neither is keen for Tom to go but he has to.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>We follow a reluctant Tom out on to -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="4" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="3" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. LANDING - NIGHT - CONTINUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom locks the bedroom door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He goes downstairs to -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="5" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="3" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. HALLWAY - NIGHT - CONTINUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>A table has been placed against the front door. Tom takes a moment to check it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Then heads into -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="6" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="3" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Kitchen - night - coNTINUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom picks up a transistor radio from the table and turns it on. It makes no noise.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>From a bottle of whisky, he takes two nerve-steadying gulps before examining the jamb of the pantry door where pencil marks indicate the growth of a child over time.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>After a few moments of contemplation, he raises the bottle to the unknown child and takes a couple more swigs.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Then he puts the bottle down and goes outside into -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="7" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="4" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. Back garden - night - contiNUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom locks the kitchen door behind himself.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He inspects an ants nest in the corner of his patio. Watches dispassionately as the ants go about their business.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>His transistor radio starts pumping out a series of bleeps, each about one second apart.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BLEEP...... BLEEP...... BLEEP......</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The sound is somewhat reminiscent of Sputnik.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The interval between bleeps gradually narrows as the bleeps grow louder and more urgent.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BLEEP...! BLEEP...! BLEEP...!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom hurries into - </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="8" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="5/8" Page="4" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Shed - night - contiNUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>An old mattress and a couple of pillows have been placed on the floor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BLEEP...! BLEEP...! BLEEP...!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The bleeps are about a tenth of a second apart now.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Anxiety is writ large on Tom’s face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He throws himself onto the mattress and places the transistor radio close to his ear.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BLEEP...! BLEEP...! BLEEP...!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom braces himself. Grits his teeth</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The bleeps rise to a crescendo. Tom fights to control his terror. He claws at the mattress. Buries his face in a pillow.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The bleeps blend one into the other as the shed suddenly fills with sickly green light.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom thrashes. Spasms.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>From the radio comes a single, unending tone:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BLEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEP!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom opens his mouth to scream. But before he can make a sound -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Right" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="5.50" RightIndent="7.10" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Transition">
      <Text>BLACKOUT:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="9" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="5" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. Back garden - morning</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Right" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="5.50" RightIndent="7.10" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Transition">
      <Text>FADE IN:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>To the sound of BIRD SONG and a CLOSE-UP of the ants nest.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Camera PANS OUT. Takes in the rest of the garden. Seems like just another ordinary day in suburbia until -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The peace is disturbed by the shed door being abruptly pushed open.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom, looking like he’s barely slept, staggers out of the shed. Trips. Lands on his knees.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>At first, he doesn’t bother getting up. He takes long, deep breaths of morning air.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>In the distance -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>GUN SHOTS. POLICE SIRENS. More GUN SHOTS.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>SILENCE.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom barely reacts to these intimations of violence. Not so the sound of GROANING which draws his attention to a badly mutilated INTRUDER sitting against the garden fence with his guts spilled on his lap.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom betrays no emotion as he briefly disappears behind the shed and returns with a garden spade.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Standing over the Intruder, he raises the spade. Brings it swiftly down, catching the Intruder on the side of his neck.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He strikes again and again - hacking at the Intruder’s neck until his head flies off.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Casting aside the spade, Tom drags the Intruder’s body into the rhubarb patch. As he does so, we see the legs of another DEAD MAN sticking out from the rhubarb.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom takes the Intruder’s head and tosses it into the rhubarb patch.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>His brutal act of killing has invigorated Tom. Panting, smiling grimly, he leans against the shed and masturbates vigorously. The resulting orgasm arrives quickly and is intense.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>After adjusting his dress, Tom makes his way to the garden tap. Turns on the tap. Washes his face. Drinks.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom dries his hands and face with his tracksuit top.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>A distant SCREAM OF HORROR is followed by the SOUND OF BREAKING GLASS, both of which Tom ignores.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He unlocks the kitchen door and goes into -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="10" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="6" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. KiTCHEN - moRNING - continuous</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Through the kitchen into -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="11" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="6" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. HALLWAY - morning - continuous</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom quickly checks that the front door is still intact and the table is undisturbed. Then he goes upstairs to -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="12" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="6" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. LANDING - morning - conTINUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom unlocks the bedroom door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Hesitates.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Full of trepidation, he opens the door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Goes into the -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="13" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="6" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BARBARA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. BedROOM - moRNING - conTINUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>As Tom enters Barbara - much to his relief - is still trussed up on the bed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Barbara</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>About bloody time. I need a piss.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="14" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="6" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRODY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Living room - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara, dressed in a red tracksuit, is on the settee, knitting baby booties while watching Dan Brody on the Great British Shopping Experience channel.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BRODY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey, hey, hey! Dan Brody here, folks - back to lavish upon you a veritable cornucopia of consumer goodies! Before we get started though, I have to pass on the sad news that my Great British Shopping Experience co-star and dear, dear friend, Hannah Newton, did not survive the last transit, so she won't be joining us today - or indeed ever again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hannah, my love, I'm sure you can hear me from up there in that Great Shopping Mall in the Sky and I want you to know that everyone here at the Great British Shopping Experience and your thousands upon thousands of fans are missing you already. Also, Martin is sincerely sorry that he gouged out your eyes and ate your liver. He knows that was very naughty of him and he says he hopes you didn’t suffer too much.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>( beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>But even with Hannah gone, life goes on and so do the bargains on the Great British Shopping Experience - case in point being this authentic reproduction Fabergé egg which is an exact copy of one in the Paris Louvre that used to belong to none other than the Empress Josephine herself.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh yes, I can hear your </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">ooh</Text>
      <Text>s and </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">aah</Text>
      <Text>s from here. Just imagine how green with envy your friends will be when they see this magnificent work of art sitting on your mantelpiece.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Bored and having no interest in acquiring an ornamental egg, Barbara sighs and puts away her knitting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Then she takes herself out to - </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="15" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 1/8" Page="7" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BARBARA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Kitchen - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara gets out the ingredients of a decent fried breakfast - eggs, bacon, sausages, tomatoes, black pudding, mushrooms.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>She throws them in a frying pan on the gas stove and watches them sizzle.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Now and then she flips over a food item with a spatula.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara is truly content.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>But then - </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The stove goes out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Alarmed, Barbara turns the gas off and back on. She tries lighting it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Nothing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>There is no gas.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Dazed, defeated, she sits at the kitchen table and sobs.  A great reservoir of suppressed fear and frustration is released in a tsunami of emotion.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom enters. He is wearing a blue track suit and drying his hair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Immediately taking stock of the situation, throws the towel over the back of a chair. Plays with the gas stove trying to get it to light. Gives up on the stupid thing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He grabs a bowl from the cupboard. Pours the contents of the frying pan into the bowl. Puts the bowl in the microwave and turns on the microwave.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Then he sits opposite Barbara and takes her hands in his.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Barbara</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s not my fault.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why don’t you go watch the telly, Barbara? I’ll bring you a nice cup of tea and some toast.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No bread.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I think we have Ryvita.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’d prefer cereal.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Cereal it is.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Cornflakes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sure.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="16" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 1/8" Page="8" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BARBARA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Living room - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom and Barbara are seated at the table. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara, whose mood has improved since the kitchen incident, has a bowl of cornflakes and a cup of tea in front of her. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom is faced with a soggy mass of half-fried breakfast items that have been microwaved.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(playful)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Go on then. Eat up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You first, my sweet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>OK.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara scoops up a spoonful of cornflakes, chews and swallows.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Barbara (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(daring him)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now you, Tom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>With a forced grin, Tom uses his fork to pick up some of his breakfast. He pops it in his mouth.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Obviously not enjoying it, he chews and swallows.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hmm. Delicious.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Have some more.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom pats his stomach.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m full, Barbara. Couldn't eat another thing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, no point wasting good food. Stick it in the fridge. You can have it for your supper.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You, my dear, are a bloody sadist.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Says the man who ties his wife up every night.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom points to something in his bowl.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I think that used to be a mushroom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="17" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6 2/8" Page="9" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHERI"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="FREDDY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KYLE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Tom’s office - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The spare bedroom. Tom has a PC set up on a desk. Also in the room are an armchair and a television.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom signs into an online work meeting. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>His PC screen is divided into four quarters. In one, he can see himself sat at his PC. The other three are each occupied by one of his work colleagues. These are KYLE Lynton, CHERI Mahler and FREDDY Benedict.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>As Tom joins, Freddy and Kyle are in the middle of a conversation.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It the only thing that makes sense, Kyle. The Soviets were lightyears ahead of the Americans and if you believe that bullshit about Neil Armstrong being the first man on the moon, you’re every bit as dumb as you look.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Kyle</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let’s see if I’ve got this straight, you fucking loon. You’re saying the Nazis built a base on the moon in 1945 and five years later the Soviets followed suit?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yep. And every time the Americans sent a probe up there, </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Hitler</Text>
      <Text> had it shot down.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>KYLE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Hitler</Text>
      <Text>? Oh for fuck’s sake, you’re having me on, aren’t you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You don’t think </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Addie</Text>
      <Text> and Eva really celebrated their honeymoon by taking cyanide, do you? It’s a documented fact that they were the first couple to fuck on the moon.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>KYLE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now I know you’re winding me up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Had you going though, didn’t I?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If you kids have quite finished talking total bollocks, perhaps we can get on with the meeting?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>KYLE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Morning, Tom! You look like shit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And you’re full of it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Cheri</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Before we get started, I have some sad news to impart.  You've probably noticed John Wickerby isn't with us today. I’m afraid he won't be with us tomorrow either - or in fact ever again. In the early hours of this morning, he shot himself in the head with a nail gun.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>KYLE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Dead?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Very.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>During last night’s transit, John attacked both his children, leaving one of them dead and the other missing half her face. When he came out of his fugue and saw what he'd done, he smothered the surviving child with a pillow. He then killed his wife by slitting her throat with a Stanley knife before doing the same to his dog.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>freddy</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Not Buddy? I really liked Buddy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>He called me on </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Skype</Text>
      <Text> to tell me what he’d done. Then right there - right in front of me - he picked up a nail gun, shouted </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">‘E.T</Text>
      <Text>. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">fuck</Text>
      <Text> off’ and shot a nail into his right </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">earhole</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Kyle</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And that was enough to kill him?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No. So he shot himself in the eye.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Silence follows as the conference attendees take in the news.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Then -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>KYLE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I call dibs on his parking space.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You callous, unfeeling shit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Frankly, Kyle, I hope when we meet tomorrow Cheri will be telling us how you were found with your throat ripped out and a rat feasting on your genitalia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>KYLE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Not me, baby. If one person is going to survive this shit show, it's Kyle Alexander Lynton esquire.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>A man you've worked with for over a decade has killed himself. His wife is dead. His children are dead. And you're calling dibs on his parking space!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>KYLE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you know who else has died in the past twenty four hours, Freddy? An estimated fifty million people.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thanks to that fucking satellite, over a billion people have died in the past few days and you expect me to get weepy eyed over a neurotic accounts manager with a personality deficiency, his - let’s face it - barely </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">shagable</Text>
      <Text> wife and a couple of brats who look like what happens when cousins marry? </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>John’s gone. Well </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">boo-bloody-hoo</Text>
      <Text>. Nobody told him to fill his brain with metal. That was his choice and I’m having his parking space whether you like it or not.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Closing her eyes and placing her hands over her ears, Cheri screams.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Stop it, stop it, stop it!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Kyle</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Jeez, Cheri. Chill. We were only joshing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No we weren’t.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ChERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re fired, Kyle.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Kyle</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You what?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You are no longer an employee of Lovecraft Wonder Toys. Pack up your shit and go.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>KYLE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You can’t do that, Cheri. Who the fuck do you -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>With a click of a mouse, Cheri unceremoniously ejects Kyle from the meeting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Anyone else want to tell me what I can and can’t do?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(clapping)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well done, Cheri. The little shit had that coming.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Perhaps now we can get on with the meeting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>First up is a meeting I had last night with the marketing department. It’s been decided to mothball Sister Gabriella and Father Dominique.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What? You’ve got to be shitting us. Gabby and Dom are the most popular dolls in retail history.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">Were</Text>
      <Text>, Freddy. Were. Our three biggest buyers have cancelled all future orders for both dolls and we’re expecting others to follow suit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>But why in God’s name? Why?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Because we’re fucked, Freddy. Well and truly fucked. The world is going down the crapper and the last thing your average kiddy wants in the middle of a cannibal apocalypse is the chance to play with a vigilante nun.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CheRI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Spot on, Tom. Thanks to the Black Knight, there’s been a seismic change in the toy market. We either adapt or die. So, after some hasty market research, our braniacs in development have come up with this.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Cheri clicks her mouse. Up pops a picture of a chainsaw-wielding, leather-jacketed doll.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ChERI (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Gentlemen, may I introduce the latest addition to the Lovecraft Wonder Toys family of dolls - the one and only Butcher Baby!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>A moment’s silence as Tom and Freddy take in what they’re seeing and hearing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Then -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Fucking hell! That’s beautiful.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s monstrous.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Cheri</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s beautiful </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">and</Text>
      <Text> monstrous and it’s going to outsell every other doll in history.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No sane parent is going to buy something like that for their kids.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Show me a sane parent and I’ll show you someone who hasn’t been paying attention. With all the shit that’s been going on, anyone not at least slightly bonkers has something seriously wrong with them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Besides which, when did parents have any say in what they buy their kids? They might not like Butcher Baby but when that little brat of theirs starts screaming, “I want a Butcher Baby! I want a Butcher Baby!” out comes that bank card and - </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">kerching!</Text>
      <Text> - there goes another Butcher Baby.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s called pester power, Freddy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Pester power!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I have to be honest. I can’t bloody wait to get my hands on one of those things.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Bit old to be playing with dolls, aren’t you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I'm going to buy me a dozen. No - two dozen. And I’m going to steal my neighbour’s gnomes and replace them with Butcher Babies.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Cheri</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>As usual, we’ll be creating a comic strip to promote the new brand. Tom, as you’re the only comic strip wallah on the team who hasn’t died in a disgusting manner, I’m leaving that in your capable hands. How soon can you knock up some panels?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll have something for you by close of play today. Do we have any scripts yet?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Marketing have come up with one but they want to run it through the usual focus groups before letting us loose on it. In the meantime, I suggest you use an old Sister Gabriella script.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Freddy, now that Kyle is on the scrap heap where he belongs, I’m putting you in charge of the sales drive. Think you can handle it?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Abso-bloody-lutely. I’ve been waiting a long time for this.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Put out the word to the sales force that it's double commission. You might also mention that anyone not hitting their targets is out on their arse.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now, if you’ll excuse me, gentlemen, I have another meeting to endure.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Cheri and Freddy both leave the meeting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom sits staring at his screen. Something is bothering him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Something doesn’t seem quite right.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He summons up the recording of the meeting. Rewinds it a bit. Pauses. Focuses in on Cheri. Zooms in over her shoulder - onto the cuckoo clock on the wall behind her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Smiles.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, well, well. You old sly boots.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="18" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4 6/8" Page="16" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BARBARA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRODY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="VOICE ON PHONE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="VOICE ON TELEVISION"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Living room - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara is on the settee, still knitting baby booties while watching Dan Brody extolling the dubious qualities of some worthless piece of tat.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Hearing TOM THUNDERING DOWN THE STAIRS, she hastily hides her wool and knitting needles under a cushion.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom bursts in. Excited. Gleeful.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’ll never guess what?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara mutes the sound on the television.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Barbara</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(dryly)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re off for a dirty weekend with Taylor Swift?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Better than that!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do tell.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I was in a meeting just now and something I saw on the screen was bothering me but I couldn’t work out just what. So I replayed the meeting, froze the picture and zoomed in behind Cheri. And do you know what was on the wall behind her?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The Shroud of Turin? The lost treasure of the Incas? Lord Lucan?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>A cuckoo clock!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(sarcastic)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh gee. Gosh. Pass the smelling salts, I’m going to faint.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s the exact same cuckoo clock Kyle Lynton brought back from last year’s toy fair in Switzerland. He put it up in his office and it drove us all mad. So he was ordered to take it home. Later on, he said he’d put it in his garage because his wife wouldn’t have it in the house.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And who did I see sitting in front of that cuckoo clock? Cheri Mahler - that’s who!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Kyle and Cheri are having an affair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Holy </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">shit</Text>
      <Text>! Are you sure?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>One hundred percent.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>In which case, I take back my recent barrage of sarcastic though witty utterances.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And it gets better.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It couldn’t possibly.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Right in the middle of the meeting, Cheri sacked Kyle! Can you believe it?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh to be a fly on the wall in that garage right now! I bet the two of them are having a right screaming match. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wait till I tell Freddy. He's going to piss himself!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom dashes out the door. He can be heard running up the stairs.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Barbara</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(amused)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Boys!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara returns her knitting from its hiding place. Then she turns the sound back on the television and recommences her knitting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BrODY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We've had a lot of calls from people wondering when - and indeed if - the goods they're ordering will pop through their letter box. Worry not, good people of Consumer Land. The powers that be here at the Great British Shopping Experience are on top of it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We've done a deal with a certain delivery company to see to it that your goodies get through to you come Hell or High Water. No nasty little UFO's going to stop us from supplying you with yummy, </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">scrummy</Text>
      <Text> stuff like this 9 carat gold bracelet with 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 real zirconium jewels which normally retails for over one hundred pounds - yes that's one zero zero </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">smackeroonies</Text>
      <Text> - but which can be yours (and I think we're mad offering it at this price) for a measly thirty-six quid.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes, you heard me: thirty-six quid.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Brody cups a hand over his ear.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BRODY (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What's that I hear? Could it be the sound of thousands of excited viewers getting on their phones and ringing the number at the bottom of this screen so they can get their hands on the bargain of the century? Yes! I do believe it is.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I'd be surprised if we don't sell out of these bracelets within a matter of minutes. So what are you waiting for? Phone, phone, phone - or forever regret missing out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara picks up her phone and speed dials the Great British Shopping Experience.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Voice on phone</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You are through to the Great British Shopping Experience. All our lines are busy right now but if you hold, we’ll put you through to one of our operators as soon as they’re available.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Your call is very important to us. Please hold.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>On the television, the Great British Shopping Channel is temporarily interrupted by a Government public information film.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>From the television, comes the sound of a KLAXON.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">VOICE ON TELEVISION</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Attention! Attention! The following is a Government Public Information Film containing information that could save your life.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Please watch and listen carefully.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Earth is under attack as never before.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The Black Knight satellite is an implacable menace, a weapon of war against which we have no defence. We must all do what we can to survive and to protect the ones we love.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Very little is known about the Black Knight. Even less is known about the deadly radiation it constantly spews onto our planet as it passes overhead. All we do know is that causes people to go mad and develop an insatiable appetite for human flesh.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>There is no hiding from this radiation. It passes through solid matter with ease and penetrates the ground for many miles. Even solid lead has proven to be no barrier.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The Black Knight is in orbit over the equator. It circles the planet once every 23 hours and 19 minutes, making it possible to predict where it will be at any given moment. Check social media to find out when it is due to be overhead where you are. Make a note of the time that it is due. If, for some reason, you cannot access social media, remember this: the Black Knight returns every 23 hours and 19 minutes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>As it comes closer to where you are, it will jam all radio transmissions and take over the Internet and other means of electronic media. When it does so, it broadcasts a series of bleeps on all frequencies through all media. Listen out for these bleeps. They will tell you how close the satellite is.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The nearer the satellite is to you, the louder the bleeps are and the less time there is between each of them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Regard the bleeps as a warning to take immediate action to protect yourself and those around you against the Black Knight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>When the Black Knight approaches, everyone should go to a room where they must be alone. Do not share a room with anyone - no matter how much you love them, no matter how much you trust them. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The fewer people you have within your immediate vicinity, the greater your chance of survival and the less chance there is of you becoming a flesh-eating maniac.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If you can, restrain yourself and/or those around you. This can be done, for instance, rope, string or bed sheets.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do not think that because you love someone, they are safe from you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do not think because someone loves you, you are safe from them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The madness inflicted by the Black Knight is immune to love and sentiment. We do not know why it only affects some and not others. The next time it passes, it might be you it affects - you it drives crazy. Then again, it may be your partner, you parent, even your child...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="19" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3 3/8" Page="20" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANDERSON"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BARBARA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BATES"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JACKSON"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Living rOOM - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara sits with her phone glued to her ear.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom enters with lunch on a tray.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It ain’t pretty, but it’s lunch.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara nods absently.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom sits next to her. Takes his plate and tea from the tray, places them on the floor at his feet. Puts the tray on Barbara’s lap.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He grabs the remote.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You mind?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara shrugs.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom changes the channel to BBC News. Louise BATES is at the news desk.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara looks at her lunch as if wandering what the hell it is.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BATES (on TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And now we can go live to Phoebe Anderson on College Green by the Houses of Parliament where a small group of protesters has gathered.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Phoebe, what can you tell us about what’s happening there?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ANDERSON (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, Louise, as you say and as you can see, there is a protest in progress here outside the Mother of Parliaments. It has been organised by a group calling themselves the League Against Disinformation - LAD for short - and I'm joined here by their leader, Russell Jackson.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mr. Jackson, would you care to tell our viewers why you and your colleagues have gathered here today?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>JACKSON (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes I would, Phoebe. We are letting the government know we are not buying into their bullshit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Anderson</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And what bullshit would that be?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>JACKSON (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>As if you didn't know! The media - especially you traitors at the BBC - know exactly what I am talking about. I am talking about this nonsense we're being fed vis-à-vis the so-called Black Knight satellite which amounts to the biggest hoax in history.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>There is no Black Knight satellite. It's all a con! A big, fat government lie!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You have to be an idiot to believe it. I mean, come on - an alien satellite? Little green men? The Government are lying to us and you, the media, are colluding with them in the biggest crime in human history.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ANDERSON (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>So how do you explain the massive slaughter we’re witnessing day in, day out?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>JACKSON</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mass hysteria! For decades, successive governments have been poisoning our water supply with fluoride. And you know what fluoride does, don't you? It makes people susceptible to suggestion and it makes them placid, which is why the first thing the Nazis did when they invaded a country was lace the reservoirs with fluoride.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ANDERSON</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>There’s no evidence they ever did that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>JACKSON</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Look: the fact is that there is no Black Knight, no aliens, no death ray driving us insane. It’s all lies - and you know it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>People, wake up! Stop being sheep. Do your own research.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Show me the dead bodies, the corpses piled high, the overflowing mortuaries, the mass burials. There aren’t any.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh sure, we’ve all seen the odd mutilated corpse but the fact of the matter is that the Government are taking the bodies of people who have died of natural causes and carving them up to make it look like they’ve been savagely attacked. What we are seeing here are the opening shots of a war against humanity, against civilisation, decency and freedom. And I want the government and all the despicable corporations behind this farce to know that we are on to them and we are prepared to fight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We the people will not be lied to any more. The revolution has begun!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Me and these brave and wonderful people behind me are staying right where we are tonight. We will maintain a vigil from dusk to dawn and we will not run for cover nor will we tie each other up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Come back tomorrow and you'll find us still here, still alive, still standing. Because there is no Black Knight! No alien satellite making us all crazy!'</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What a nut job. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Maybe he’s right. Maybe it is all a hoax.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re not serious.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Show me the satellite, Tom. Then tell me how any machine - alien or not - could make people turn to murder and cannibalism. Tell me how it could possibly affect the short-term memory of billions of people so they can’t remember what they just did. And tell me why there’s no recording - not a single video - of what supposedly happens when the satellite comes along. I’d like to know, Tom. You’re smart - or at least you say you are - so tell me how -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(into phone)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh hello. Yes. The bracelet. You have some left?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thank goodness. It’s taken so long to get through, I was worried you might have sold out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I quite understand. These are difficult times.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Exasperated, Tom switches of the television and takes his lunch out of the room.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes I am. My membership number GSE3287351... That’s right. Mrs Barbara Caxton.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s a VISA card... The long number is -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="20" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 3/8" Page="24" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHERI"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. TOM’S OFFICE - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom is at his desk, finishing off a mock-up comic panel for Butcher Baby on his </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">iPad</Text>
      <Text>. It depicts Butcher Baby holding up the head of a freshly decapitated nun.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>His work is interrupted by a Zoom call from Cheri.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hi, Tom. Just wanted to check in to see how things are coming along.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ve got a fistful of panels I think you’ll like. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He holds up his </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">iPad</Text>
      <Text> to the camera on his PC.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This one I’m especially proud of. I got the inspiration for it from Antonio Canova's famous statue, “Perseus with the Head of Medusa”.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ChERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m loving it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I thought it might be funny to have him slay Sister Gabby - put the sanctimonious bitch out of our misery.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sounds great. Just one thing though, Tom. Why do you assume Butcher Baby's a “him”?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Isn’t he? Or she? Or whatever?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It's not been decided as yet. My thinking is that we should make him/her transgender whereas Dave Ashton (dinosaur that he is) wants two versions of Butcher Baby - one male, one female. He says they can be differentiated by the </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">colour</Text>
      <Text> of their chainsaws: blue for Boy Butcher Baby and pink for Girl Butcher Baby. I told him he was being unspeakably sexist but he said he didn't care because stereotyping sells dolls and I have to agree with him on that one, which is why I strongly believe transgender is the way to go.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What do you think, Tom?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Transgender</Text>
      <Text> sounds good to me. And I’ll tell you what would be a hoot, Cheri - something that will really turbo-boost our sales. How about if we gave him - or her - the ability to transition. He could start off as a boy and then at the press of a button - hey presto! - he’s a girl. Then another press and he's a boy again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I like it, Tom. I really do. Only I'm not sure it's feasible. I mean it would need some quite intricate machinery to turn its penis into a vagina and back again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I was thinking more along the lines of a detachable penis.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you kidding me? That's the dumbest idea I've heard in a long time. You can't put a detachable penis on a child's toy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t see why not.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Two words, Tom: choking hazard!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh yeah. I hadn’t thought of that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If you can get those panels over to me this evening, that would be great. Otherwise tomorrow morning will do. In the meantime, I'm e-mailing you a couple of designs I want you to keep under your hat for now.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>For Butcher Baby?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>For Butcher Baby's friends. If Butcher Baby sells as well as you and I both know it will, then we'll follow up with a range of complementary dolls. Barbie has Ken. Sindy has Paul. And Butcher Baby will have Psycho Sam and Man-Hater Mandy. What do you think?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Genius, Cheri. Utter fucking genius.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Isn’t it?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>By the way, Tom, I've decided to reinstate Kyle. He may be a dick, but he’s </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">our</Text>
      <Text> dick for the sake of the project, we need him aboard. I hope you understand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh sure, Cheri. I understand all right.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="21" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="26" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Kitchen - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom enters. Swigs at the whisky. Picks up and turns on the transistor radio.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Goes out to -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="22" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="26" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. back GARDEN - night - continuous</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom locks the kitchen door and heads straight to the shed. Along the way, the radio starts bleeping.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BLEEP... BLEEP... BLEEP...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="23" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="27" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Shed - NIGHT - continuous</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>In the shed, Tom lies on the mattress, transistor radio in hand, and nervously awaits the coming of the Black Knight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The radio starts to BLEEP.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The bleeps grow louder and louder, more and more urgent.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BLEEP...! BLEEP...! BLEEP...!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom sweats. Fights to control his terror.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BLEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEP!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Green light fills the shed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom convulses. Opens his mouth to scream.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Right" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="5.50" RightIndent="7.10" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Transition">
      <Text>BLACKOUT:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="24" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="27" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. back GARDEN - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">FADE IN.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The Black Knight has just this moment passed by. We are outside its influence.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>A green glow on the horizon thins then vanishes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>As suburbia surfaces from its fugue, dogs BARK. CAR and BURGLAR ALARMS sound. Lights go on in nearby houses.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom, bedraggled and befuddled, stumbles out of his shed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He stands in the middle of the garden, looking up at the Milky Way, displaying a gamut of emotions - awe, loathing, fear...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Distant GUN SHOTS bring him back to earth.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He unlocks the kitchen door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Goes into - </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="25" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="27" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Kitchen - NIGHT - coNTINUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom takes a swig of whisky.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Goes out to -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="26" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="27" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. HallWAY - NIGHT - conTINUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom checks the front door and table then hurries up the stairs to -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="27" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="28" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Landing - NIGHT - conTINUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom unlocks the bedroom door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Enters -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="28" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="28" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BARBARA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. BEDROOM - NIGHT - coNTINUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>As Tom comes in, Barbara (tied up as usual) eyes him warily.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If you’ve come to eat my liver, I’m afraid we’re all out of onions. You’ll have to make do with fava beans.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s not funny.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wasn’t supposed to be. What time is it?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>About 3 o’clock.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>At night?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The Black Knight's not long since gone. Would you like me to untie you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(sarcastic)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No. I would like you to leave me trussed up so I can spend a delightful few hours pretending to be a Christmas turkey.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(turning to leave)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh. OK.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You get back here, Tom Caxton, or I’ll rip your bollocks off.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom makes a start on untying Barbara.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BarBARA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How’s that little soldier, of yours?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Pumped up and ready for action, ma’am.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Good. Because as soon as I get my circulation back, I’m going to want a right good seeing to.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="29" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 7/8" Page="29" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BATES"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="VOLKOV"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. LiVING ROOM - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom and Barbara are watching the television from the sofa.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Louise Bates is presenting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Bates (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>These pictures appear to show a Saturn V rocket about to be launched from Cape Canaveral.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And I’m just hearing that the White House have confirmed that at approximately 9 P.M. Eastern Daylight Time - that's 1 A.M. GMT - NASA launched a Saturn V from Cape Canaveral but have so far declined to give any reason for doing so.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>ON TELEVISION: Night time launch of a Saturn V with commentary from NASA Ground Control.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>We follow the launch to just before the picture cuts to the watching crowd.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Bates  (ON TV) (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Our science correspondent Professor Leonid Volkov from the University of Essex has joined us online to talk about this astonishing development. First of all, where the hell did the Americans get a fully functioning Saturn V rocket from?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>On television: CAMERA cuts to Leonid VOLKOV.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Volkov</Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""> (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That is the 64 million dollar question and I don't really have an answer, Louise. When the Apollo moon program came to its untimely end, the Americans had built a total of 16 Saturn Vs, 13 of which were launched into space. The remaining three were distributed to various museums. Having said that, clearly there must have been at least one more Saturn V which for reasons I find hard to fathom was kept secret from the public. Unlike the three museum pieces, the American government must have spent millions every year for more than half a century keeping it in workable condition and now they bring it out of mothballs and shoot it into space. Seems crazy to me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Bates (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes, it is hard to make sense of. Clearly, this has something to do with the Black Knight satellite.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>VOLKOV (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That would be the obvious conclusion.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Bates (ON TV) </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is it possible that its payload is some sort of top secret weapon which they believe can put paid to the Black Knight?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>VOLKOV (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Da, it's possible but who can say? And even if it is a weapon, there is no guarantee that it will be effective. Remember, we have thrown several gigatons of atomic warheads at this beast and what good has it done? We might as well be using bows and arrows.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Bates (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, let's hope you're wrong, Professor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>VOLKOV (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Da. Let’s hope.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Bates (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Professor Leonid Volkov, thank you for your time.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>VOLKOV (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Whatever.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Bates (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And now we're going live by news drone to College Green and viewers are warned that this report will contain graphic images that some might find deeply upsetting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>As you can see, there's Big Ben in the background and beyond that the River Thames. Now the drone is descending towards College Green, using its spotlight to pick out the grisly details of the grim tragedy that unfolded there tonight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You may recall that a group calling themselves the League Against Deception had assembled on the green to protest against an alleged conspiracy. Their leader, Russell Jackson, told our reporter that he and his followers believed the Black Knight phenomenon to be a hoax and they intended to prove it by ignoring official advice and staying on the green during tonight’s transit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And this is the result: dead bodies everywhere. So far, we've counted a dozen but there are probably more - not to mention a number of walking wounded.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>As we get up close on this dead protestor here, you can see his face frozen in a look of abject terror. And next to him is someone who's been disembowelled and it looks like a good deal of their intestines have been eaten.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>None of the dead have been identified as yet. Those blue flashing lights are from a couple of police cars and an ambulance that have just arrived on the scene. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Russell Jackson, the group’s leader, is not believed to be amongst those who lost their lives in what was a quite avoidable tragedy. We hope to catch up with him as soon as possible to get his reaction to this bloody mess, which - let's face it - is by and large his fault. It would be interesting to see if he's changed his mind about the Black Knight being a hoax.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Incidentally, those things moving about on the edge of the picture are rats enjoying a breakfast of freshly-served human flesh.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="30" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 5/8" Page="32" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BOB FROM WOLVERHAMPTON"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KATIE FROM BLACKPOOL"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TATE"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. Back garden - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom sits himself on the patio with a bar of chocolate which he bites into now and then. He takes out his transistor radio and switches it on. Tunes to Galaxy Talk Radio and the Ken TATE Phone-In Show.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BOB FROM WOLVERHAMPTON is shooting his mouth off.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BOB from wolverhampton (on Radio)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>All I'm saying is that it's nonsense to say that the Black Knight was sent by God to punish the gays.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tate (ON radio)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Amen to that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BOB from wolverhampton (ON RADIO)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I mean it's not as if there's anything new about men doing disgusting things with other men. That sort of thing goes back to the ancient Greeks. God didn't much mind it back then, so why should he mind it now?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No, what's changed, James, is the way certain people are making a mockery of God by claiming there are more than two genders despite what the Bible says.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Even when the Sodomites, the pedos and the commies were doing their worst, God was more than happy to leave us alone - apart from the odd earthquake or tsunami to punish the atheists - but with men claiming to be women and women acting like they were born with penises, is it any wonder he's mad at us?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I'm willing to bet, James, that everyone who's died because of the Black Knight is transgendered - in thought if not in deed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tate (ON RADIO)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>OK, Bob. I've run out of tin foil so I'm going to have to cut you off there.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That was Bob from Wolverhampton. Keep taking the pills, Bob.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And next on the line is Katie, a housewife from Blackpool, Lancashire.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Go ahead, Katie. You have the ears of the nation.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>KATIE FROM BLACKPOOL gets to have her say.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Katie FROM BLACKPOOL (ON RADIO)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thank you, Ken. I just wanted to ask why it is that with thousands  of nuclear weapons in the world - all those rockets and missiles that have cost us billions and billions of pounds - we haven’t been able to shoot down the Black Knight. We keep hearing all sorts of excuses but they all sound ridiculous to me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TATE (ON RADIO)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, Katie, according to the governments of both the United States and Russia, numerous attempts have been made to nuke the satellite but to no avail.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>KATIE FROM BLACKPOOL (ON RADIO)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And do you believe that crap? These are nuclear weapons we’re talking about. Some of them are supposedly powerful enough to totally destroy a city as big as London and yet they can’t destroy something not much bigger than a family car?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tate (ON RADIO)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The problem is that the Black Knight is not exactly defenceless. It appears to be surrounded by a forcefield which causes missiles to self-destruct while they’re too far away from the satellite to damage it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>KATIE FROM BLACKPOOL (ON RADIO)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>But they’re nukes! We’re told they get to within a quarter of a mile of the Black Knight before they go off. That’s got to be close enough, hasn’t it?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tate</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let me finish, Katie. Outer space isn’t London or Hiroshima or Bikini Atoll. As I understand it, most of the damage done by nuclear weapons comes from the blast wave. In space, where there’s no atmosphere, you don’t get a blast wave, which means for a nuke to be of any use against the Black Knight it has to explode right in its face, as it were.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Katie FROM BLACKPOOL (ON RADIO)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, lasers then. What about lasers?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TATE (ON RADIO)h</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What about them?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>KATIE FROM BLACKPOOL (ON RADIO)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ronald Reagan promised the U.S. was going to build lasers powerful enough to punch holes in the moon. That was over fifty years ago. So where are these lasers and why aren’t they using them?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TATE (ON RADIO)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>To be honest with you, Katie, that’s a question I can’t give a good answer to. If any of my listeners out there are privy to American military secrets, perhaps you could give us a call. The number to ring is -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom turns off the radio.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He spits out a half-chewed piece of chocolate. It lands on the lawn. He watches with grim fascination as it is mobbed by ants.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="31" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 4/8" Page="34" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ISABELLE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Bathroom - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara, on her hands and knees, is bent over the toilet bowl puking her guts out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>When she’s done, she sits with her back against the wall, stomach on belly, looking content.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>INT. TOM’S OFFICE - DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom, his mood gloomy, enters and slumps into his chair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>His phone rings. He answers.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tom Caxton.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>On the other end of the line is ISABELLE Lynton.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ISABELLE (ON THE PHONE)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mr. Caxton, you probably don’t remember me though we did meet once. I’m Isabelle Lynton.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh yes. Kyle’s wife.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ISABELLE (ON THE PHONE)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Would you like a good laugh, Mr. Caxton?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I can't imagine there's anything can make me laugh right now, but you're welcome to try.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ISABELLE (ON THE PHONE)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s about my husband. As you know, the man’s a complete and utter shit with the morals of a warthog on heat. A couple of days ago, I caught him in bed with your boss, Cheri Mahler.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ve always known about his philandering and I’ve tolerated it - not liked it, mind; just tolerated it - so long as he gave me every opportunity to pretend it wasn’t happening. But this was my bed he was fucking his whore in. My bed in my house right next to the room where my children sleep!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll spare you the details of what I said to him and his tart and skip to the part where I packed my bags, picked up my kids from school and skedaddled off to my parents.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And if you’re thinking, “this isn’t very funny. When are you going to make me laugh like you promised, Mrs. Lynton?”, hang on to your hat because here it comes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Last night, just after the Black Knight had been and gone, I got a phone call. When I saw it was from Kyle, I nearly didn’t answer, but curiosity got the better of me and I’m glad it did - and when I say glad, I mean ecstatic. There’s no sweeter sound, Mr. Caxton, than the sound of a philandering husband screeching like a little girl being force-fed worms.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">My penis!</Text>
      <Text> he screamed. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">My penis, my penis, my penis! The bitch has bitten off my penis!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Isabelle cracks up with laughter, sounding more hysterical with each passing second.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom is appalled.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>IsABELLE  (ON THE PHONE) (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(laughing)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">My penis!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom smiles.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ISABELLE  (ON THE PHONE) (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(laughing)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">She’s got my penis in her mouth!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>In spite of himself, Tom chuckles.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ISABELLE (ON THE PHONE) (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(laughing)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">Oh my God! She’s chewing it!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Isabelle cackles. It is too much for Tom. He joins in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Great big belly laughs. Tears streaming down his cheeks.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ISABELLE  (ON THE PHONE) (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(laughing)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">And now she’s choking!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The two laugh uncontrollably until their mirth runs its course.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>They catch their breath.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ISABELLE  (ON THE PHONE) (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m calling from the hospital. They’ve had to incinerate what little of Kyle’s penis Cheri left him. Apparently they can grow him a new one - isn’t science wonderful? - but there’s been such a spate of men having their dicks bitten off he’s going to have to wait at least three years, by which time I’ll be a happy divorcee.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thank you for sharing that with me, Mrs. Lynton. It was just the tonic I needed. But I’m curious as to why you chose me of all people to share your good news with.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ISABELLE (ON THE PHONE)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Don’t flatter yourself, Mr. Caxton. Your name just happened to be on Kyle’s mobile phone. I plan to spend the next few hours going through his contact list, letting everyone and his brother know that my husband no longer has a penis.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Isabelle cuts the connection.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="32" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="5" Page="37" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BARBARA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRODY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CAVELL"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Living room - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara, as usual, is glued to the Great British Shopping Experience.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BRODY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Quick, quick, quick, folks, because this one is definitely going to sell out in a flash. He who hesitates has lost the bargain of a lifetime.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>“Well, what is it, Dan?” I hear you say. “Tell us, you incredibly charismatic television person, you.”</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It is - drum roll - a straightjacket - perfect for restraining that special someone in your life.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And I’ve just had a voice in my ear telling me we have to break for a news flash - something we’ve never before had to do here at the Great British Shopping Experience Channel. It better be bloody important, else I’m going to be very cross!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Don’t go away. We’ll be right back.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Television cuts to a screen with the following message:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Bold">An important announcement from the Prime Minister for every inhabitant of the United Kingdom will follow shortly.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Bold">This announcement is to be broadcast on all available channels.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Bold">Stay tuned.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The picture cuts to Prime Minister Arthur CAVELL, sat at a desk in a well-appointed office.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>CAPTION on the television: </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Bold">The Right Honourable Arthur Cavell, Prime Minister </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Cavell</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>My fellow citizens, as none of you can fail to be aware, this nation, along with every other nation across every continent, is facing an unprecedented crisis, the enormity of which cannot be overstated.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Five days ago, something strange began to happen and is continuing to happen, causing each and every one of us to black out at regular intervals and in many cases commit horrendous acts of murder and cannibalism.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The source of this phenomenon has been pinpointed. It is a satellite of unknown origin, design and purpose commonly known as the Black Knight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Numerous attempts to bring down this vile artefact have failed and so the killings go on and will go on for the foreseeable future.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>In these desperate times, desperate remedies are called for and it is therefore my unpleasant duty to announce the immediate commencement of martial law in the United Kingdom along with a 24 hour curfew. All civilians are hereby ordered to remain indoors unless specifically exempted. Any breech of this order will be considered High Treason and punishable by death. The army and police now have the authority to use lethal force as they see fit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let me make this clear. Unless you have been told otherwise, you must not venture out of doors. Anyone doing so is liable to summary execution. There are no exceptions.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is total lockdown. Stay indoors or suffer the consequences!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Stunned, Tom switches off the television. Sits shaking his head.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Barbara</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tom?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I tried to order some earrings.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Beautiful earrings with cultured pearls.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Earrings? Did you not just hear the Prime Minister declare martial law?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I tried to buy a pair. The transaction was declined. It’s your credit card. I think it’s maxed out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hardly surprising the way you’ve been spending.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ring them, will you, Tom?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ring who?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The credit card company. Ask them to increase your credit limit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You have got to be shitting me, Barbara. Don’t you understand? Don’t you get what’s happening?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It can’t harm to ask.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>There’s nobody to ask. You saw me yesterday trying to call the bank. No answer. You saw me trying to call the gas company. No answer. I tried to call my mother, the police, even the fucking Samaritans. No fucking answer! About the only people answering their phones is that shitty shopping channel you’re always fucking glued to!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>There’s no need to swear. I don’t know what you’re getting upset about. If they say no then no it is. I’ll dip into my savings.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You call them. The number’s on the phone. I bet you won’t have to wait five seconds to get through. I bet straightaway they’ll say “Oh sure we’ll increase your husband’s credit limit. How much would you like? Ten thousand pounds? A hundred thousand? How about a million fucking quid!’</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tom, stop it. You’re scaring me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m scaring you? Me? We’re in the middle of a cannibal apocalypse and the thing you’re scared off is me? Your own fucking husband?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara breaks down. Buries her face in her hands.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Stop it! Please stop it. I just want to buy something nice before I die. Is that too much to ask?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom relents. His anger is spent.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re not going to die. I won’t let it happen.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re going to kill me, Tom. I know you are. And if you don’t kill me, I’ll kill you because that’s the way it is. People are killing the people they love.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Not you. Not me. That sort of evil isn’t inside either of us.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why not? Because we’re English and middle-class and living in suburbia where everyone is so fucking nice to each other? Because we buy the Guardian and I bake cakes for the </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Womens</Text>
      <Text> Institute? Because unlike everyone else on this planet we’re not the end result of millions of years of evolution punctuated by savagery and genocide and survival of the fittest?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re going a bit crazy, </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Babs</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Exactly. I’m going crazy. You’re going crazy. The whole fucking world’s going crazy. Nobody’s sane any more. Nobody!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It will end, Barbara. They’ll find a way to destroy the Black Knight and everything will get back to normal</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How will they destroy it? They’ve thrown half the nukes in the world at it and haven’t even scratched the paint work.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(</Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">beat</Text>
      <Text>)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know full well where this is heading. Lie to yourself all you like. But don’t lie to me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m not lying.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara shoves Tom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Liar! You’re a bloody liar, Tom Caxton. We’re going to die! You know we’re going to die! Just admit it, can’t you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Pack it in, Barbara.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Say it, Tom. Say we’re going to die - you, me and every human being on this planet. We’re going to die, we’re going to die, we’re going to die!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom slaps Barbara.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Stop it!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom, realising what he’s done, is appalled at himself.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Barbara, I’m sorry. I’m just so -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara gleefully throws herself on Tom. There is something feral about her as she ravishes him, pulling his hair, kissing him fiercely.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>At first, Tom is paralysed with confusion. It is only when Barbara viciously bites his ear that he responds with animal passion.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom and Barbara wrestle. Hands all over each other. Tearing at each other’s clothing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>They make love with wild abandon.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="33" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 1/8" Page="42" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BARBARA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRODY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JACKSON"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="NEWS PRESENTER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="PHOEBE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TELEVISION PRESENTER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="VOLKOV"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. living room - later</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom and Barbara at the table playing Monopoly. Their faces display signs of their bout of rough sex.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The television is on, displaying a notice: </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Bold">The Great British Shopping Experience is temporarily off-air. We will be back as soon as possible.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Barbara</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We’re almost out of food.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I think the Keplers are dead.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Who?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The people next door. Mr. and Mrs. Kepler. The old couple.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>So that’s their name? Kepler. I never knew that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll try their house when it gets dark.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Barbara</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>They’re not likely to have much food - what with them being old and all that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>They’ll have some. It’ll have to do for now.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What if they’re not dead?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m sure they are. No harm checking.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara lands on Chance. She takes a Chance card.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Get out of jail free. Well, ain’t I the lucky one?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The GBSE Channel comes back on air.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Brody</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hello? Is anybody there? This is Dan Brody coming to you live from the studios of GBSE, the Great British Shopping Experience Channel. As you’ve no doubt gathered, we’ve been off the air for a little while but now we’re back and we aim to go on broadcasting and bringing you fantastic bargains for as long as we possibly can.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>So let’s not hang about shall we? We’ve got a lot of shopping to catch up on. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Those who were watching when we were so rudely interrupted will recall this delightful porcelain poodle imported all the way from Taiwan. We said it was worth £89 but you could have it for a mere 39 quid. Well, bollocks to that. Who’ll give me 29 quid?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No, let’s make it a fiver. Five fucking quid for the finest fucking porcelain poodle money can fucking buy. Lovingly handcrafted by pre-pubescent slaves in some oriental sweat shop. Actually, like everything else we flog here, it’s a pile of crap but that’s not going to stop you buying it, is it, you fucking morons?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>There’s the number to call at the bottom of the screen. Let’s show the aliens it’s going to take more than an apocalypse to dampen our rampant consumerism.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>By the way, in case you’re wondering what’s happened to the delightful Lorna McReady who usually fills this slot, she’s no longer with us. One of the camera crew had her kidneys for breakfast. Such a sweet girl. I bet she tasted delicious.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We’ve yet to deter -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>A power cut renders the telly inactive.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Outside, BURGLAR ALARMS go off.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>A HELICOPTER passes overhead.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh well. Nearly time for bed anyway.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="34" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="44" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. BEDROOM - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom ties up Barbara. Beds her up for the night.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="35" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="44" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. Garden - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>With his transistor radio BLEEPING, Tom hurries into -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="36" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="44" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Shed - night - conTINUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Terrified, Tom barely has time to throw himself onto the mattress before the BLEEPs become one CONTINUOUS BLEEP and the shed fills with green light.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Agony!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Right" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="5.50" RightIndent="7.10" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Transition">
      <Text>BLACKOUT:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="37" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="44" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>ext. Garden - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom - haggard, drained - emerges from the shed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He washes his face at the garden tap. Drinks.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Inspects the ant nest.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Goes indoors.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="38" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 2/8" Page="45" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANDERSON"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BARBARA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BATES"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHERI"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JACKSON"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MILLER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SERGEANT"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SOLDIER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TEDDY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Living room - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom and Barbara, both wearing red tracksuits, are watching television.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Louise Bates is presenting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Bates</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We're joining our reporter, Phoebe Anderson who has tracked down the conspiracy theorist Russell Jackson, leader of the League Against Disinformation. As you may have seen yesterday, the League held a demonstration on College Green and stayed out all night in an attempt to prove that the Black Knight is a hoax. Many of those demonstrators are now dead, having been attacked and devoured by their fellow protesters.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Phoebe, is that Mr. Jackson sitting in those bushes behind you?'</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ANDERSON</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes it is, Louise. I've cornered him here in a very deserted Hyde Park. If you listen, you'll hear something that's not been heard at this time of day in central London for hundreds of years - no traffic, no people. Here, at least, the curfew is being observed. I and Tim, my cameraman, by the way, have a special press permit which allows us to be out and about without the risk of getting shot.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>These two handsome gentlemen are Sergeants Wycliffe and Moore, an escort provided by the army for my protection.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Can we get the camera on Mr. Jackson, please?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>There, in the bushes, looking forlorn and somewhat manic is Russell Jackson, the man who yesterday assured us as to the non-existence of the Black Knight satellite.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I'm not getting any closer because last time I tried, he bit my leg.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mr. Jackson! Can you hear me? I was wondering if you'd care to share your current thoughts regarding the Black Knight satellite? Do you still insist the worldwide phenomenon that has killed millions of people and driven millions more into insanity is down to the infernal machinations of a sinister cabal out to destroy civilisation?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Vague mumblings from Jackson can be heard but not deciphered.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ANDERSON (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I'm sorry, Mr. Jackson. You'll have to speak up if you want to be heard.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Jackson</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I said damn you! You whore of Satan! I hope you burn in Hell for eternity along with all the other shit stains at the BBC.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ANDERSON</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Can you remember, Mr. Jackson, who you killed last night? Whose flesh you feasted upon? Whose blood you drank? Because that’s what happened, isn’t it? The Black Knight came and turned you into a homicidal maniac. You’ve blood on your hands, Mr. Jackson - quite literally.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>JaCKSON</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Whore! Slut! Slag! Cunt, cunt, cunt, cunt, cunt, cunt, cunt, cunt, cunt, cunt, cunt, cunt! You cunting fucking cunt!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ANDERSON</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You can't see it at home because Tim has quite rightly turned his camera away, but Mr. Jackson is now defecating on the footpath. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mr. Jackson, aren't you ashamed of yourself?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>JACKSON</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I hope your children die of cancer, you cunt-whore!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ANDERSON</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mr. Jackson, I have been asked by Sergeant Wycliffe and Sergeant Moore to inform you that you are in breach of the lockdown. As you may or may not know, the penalty for that is death.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>We hear TWO RIFLES BEING COCKED.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ANDERSON (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Goodbye, Mr. Jackson.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>TWO SHOTS ring out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom turns off the television.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t know whether to laugh or to cry.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="39" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 7/8" Page="47" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHERI"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="FREDDY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Tom’s office - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom logs into the morning conference. FREDDY is the only other participant.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tom! So glad you made it. I thought maybe I was going to be all on my lonesome here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I take it you’ve heard about Cheri and Kyle?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Freddy</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If it wasn't so funny, it would be tragic. Once this Black Knight bollocks is over, I intend to make a film about it. I was thinking Ana de </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Armas</Text>
      <Text> might make a good Cheri.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Might I suggest Kenneth </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Branagh</Text>
      <Text> for Kyle?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Freddy</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You might indeed. Now then, are we going to bother  with this meeting? Or shall we just call it a - No, wait! Cheri's dialling in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Morning, Cheri.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sorry I'm late. I've had a bit of a domestic situation to deal with.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nothing too serious I hope?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nothing I couldn't handle.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Kyle's not with us yet. I expect he'll be along later.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Knock it off, Freddy. I can tell by your smug expression you know what happened. I suppose Kyle’s bitch of a wife told you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She gave me a blow-by-blow account.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And you, Tom? Did she call you as well?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now let me think? Oh yes. She rang me up and said something about you mistaking Kyle’s penis for a hotdog sausage.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let me make one thing clear, gentlemen. What happened last night is between me and Kyle. It's not a work matter and I expect you two to act in a professional manner.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh we will, Cheri? Won’t we, Tom?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know me. Professional’s my middle name.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CheRI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Good. First order of business: our new doll, Man-Hating Mandy. I've sent both of you the specs. Have you had a chance to look at them yet?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Not yet. I've only just finished untying my wife.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FrEDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I had a quick </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">shufti</Text>
      <Text>. Just one question.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>FREDDY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What does a human penis taste like?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well done, Freddy. You've just got yourself fired.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="40" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 4/8" Page="49" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BARBARA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="K"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SERGEANT"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SOLDIER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Living room - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom and Barbara are at the dining table playing Cluedo.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Barbara</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>When things get back to normal, we should put our heads together and design a board game.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And what would this board game be about?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Zombies. Thanks to the Black Knight, there’s going to be a whole lot of interest in that sort of thing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>A bit morbid but I think you’re spot on. Remind me to tell you about Butcher Baby some time.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Picture this, Tom: a graveyard. It’ll be a bit like a Monopoly board but instead of streets and stations it’ll have graves and mausoleums and right in the middle would be a church. If you make it to the church, you’re safe, otherwise the zombies will be able to get you, suck out your brains and turn you into one of the living dead.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now, if you land on a grave that hasn’t been dug up and you have the right spell, bag yourself a corpse and create your own zombie.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Then whoever has the most zombies when the sun comes up wins.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom rolls the dice.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Eight. That brings me to the Library.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If one of your zombies lands on a square occupied by an opponent’s zombie, then the two zombies have to fight. Whoever rolls the highest number gets to suck out the other zombie’s brains.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And now I think of it, we could throw in vampires and werewolves.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s your go, Barbara.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What do you think though, Tom? I reckon we could make a killing - if you’ll pardon the expression.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Before Tom can answer, he is interrupted by a medley of noises coming from the road outside. Unseen by us, a man named Josef K is being chased by soldiers.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>We hear:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The CLANKING, CHURNING, WHIRLING of an armoured vehicle.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>RUNNING FEET</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Soldier (O.S.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Stop or we’ll shoot!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>More RUNNING FEET. Perhaps a dozen men. Coming closer.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The FRONT GATE swinging open.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>SoLDIER  (O.s.)(CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Stop or we’ll shoot!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>POUNDING on the front door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>K (O.S.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let me in! In God’s name, let me in!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>MACHINE GUN FIRE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Bullets TEARING INTO THE FRONT DOOR. Wood SPLINTERING. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>FEET RUNNING up the garden path.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Motioning for Barbara to stay put, Tom goes to the window, pressing himself against the wall.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Soldiers?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And an armoured car. There’s a dead man in the driveway. They’re dragging him away.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Straight through the hydrangeas! Thanks a bundle.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>SERGEANT (O.S.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Stay away from that window and do not come outside or you will be shot! You will not be warned again!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Jesus!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Startled, Tom hastily backs away from the window. Trips. Falls on the floor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara ducks and joins him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What the actual fuck? This is suburbia. People don’t get shot in suburbia!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>They are both silent as they listen to the armoured vehicle and the soldiers heading off down the street.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>When peace returns, they take their places at the table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom picks up the dice.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is it your go or mine?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="41" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 3/8" Page="51" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BARBARA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRODY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Living ROOM - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>On the settee, Tom and Barbara are devouring a light supper of biscuits and cocoa.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The television is tuned to the GBSE Channel.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BRODY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>OK folks. That’s got to be it for now. The Black Knight satellite is due overhead pretty soon. We here at the Great Shopping Experience Channel are off to separate rooms with as many of us locked safely away as possible and I suggest you folks out there in Consumer Land do the same.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Who knows? Maybe just for once we’ll all survive.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And in this time of perdition and uncertainty, let us pray the madness ends soon. I don't know what was in that Saturn V but something tells me it's going to put a stop to the Black Knight and its evil, evil ways.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Good night and God bless. See you all at 6 a.m. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">sharp</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>
The screen goes to the ‘off-air’ sign.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Colonel Peacock in the Library with the candlestick.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Cobblers.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I'm telling you, it was Colonel Peacock in the library with the candlestick. Kindly go check.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Can’t it wait until the morning?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And give you a chance to change what’s in the envelope? I don’t think so.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re forgetting I’ll be tied up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>All the same.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Fine. I'll go get the envelope. And as I do so, I hope you notice I'm flouncing in disgust at your vile insinuation that I would stoop so low as to cheat at board games.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara flounces to the table. Snatches the solution envelope. Opens it. Looks at the cards.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Colonel Mustard! Billiard Room! Candlestick! You weren’t even close.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh well. You can’t win ‘em all.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="42" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 4/8" Page="53" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BARBARA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Bedroom - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom is about to tie Barbara up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Get into bed with me, Tom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s not safe.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you think I don’t trust my own husband not to kill me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>There exists a distinct possibility that I might just do that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Or are you afraid you might wake up to find me sucking your brains out through a straw?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Frankly - yes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Listen, that satellite is going to keep orbiting the earth, spewing its poisonous radiation until every last one of us is dead. And if it doesn’t kill us all, what then? We’ll be living in a world of trauma and guilt - a world where there’s barely a man, woman or child who hasn’t killed someone they love and eaten human flesh.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t want to live in that world.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now get into this bed and do what a husband’s supposed to do. I’ve had enough of you slinking off to that fucking shed of yours.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Knowing when he’s beaten, Tom climbs into bed with Barbara. He turns on his transistor radio which spews out static.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If I kill you, I’ll kill myself.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s the spirit, Tom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tomorrow, I’ll get us some food from next door. I’m sure the Keplers are dead. And if they’re not, I’ll try some of the other houses.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll come with you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Too dangerous.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>So what isn’t right now? If you’re going to get shot for looting, I’m going to get shot with you. And no arguments.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We’ll see what happens.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara takes Tom’s arm. Wraps it around herself.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Barbara</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tell me about Cheri Mahler.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s there to tell?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is she insane? I mean, to bite off a man’s penis and then act as if it hadn’t happened... she can’t be right in the head.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I think she was in shock, that’s all. Right now, she’s probably having a fit of the screaming ab dabs.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You fancy her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do not.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>When I mentioned her name, I felt your penis twitch.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m lying in bed with the hottest bitch in Christendom. Of course my penis is going to twitch.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BARBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(dryly)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh Tom! You say the sweetest things.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The radio starts to BLEEP.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hell’s bells! The kitchen door. I’ve left it unlocked.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom starts to rise. Barbara restrains him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BaRBARA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I need you here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>As the </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">BLEEPING</Text>
      <Text> intensifies, Tom and Barbara hold onto each other. They are terrified.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The bleeps run into one another - </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">BLEEEEEEEEEEEEP</Text>
      <Text>! The room fills with green light.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom and Barbara open their mouths to scream but before any sound comes out -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Right" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="5.50" RightIndent="7.10" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Transition">
      <Text>BLACKOUT:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="43" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 5/8" Page="55" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MR. KEPLER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. BeDROOM - night - later</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Right" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="5.50" RightIndent="7.10" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Transition">
      <Text>FADE IN:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The Black Knight has passed. Tom and Barbara are next to each other in bed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>In the corner sits MR. KEPLER, Tom’s elderly next door neighbour. He has bits of human flesh smeared down the front of his chest and one of Barbara’s ears in his hand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom opens his eyes. Stares at the ceiling as he gets his bearings.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He has a bad feeling. Turns towards Barbara to find that half her face is missing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>She is quite dead.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom convulses. His arms, jerking like they've received a jolt of electricity, push him away from Barbara, out of the bed, against the wall, knocking the wind from him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Effortlessly, he vomits, spilling the contents of his stomach down his chin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Shock has left him shaking and all but catatonic.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>From the corner of the room, comes the small voice of Mr. Kepler.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Mr. Kepler</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m sorry.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(vaguely)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>MR. KEPLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m sorry, I’m sorry, I’m sorry.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(muttering to himself)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Too late for sorry. Sorry doesn’t cut it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>MR. KEPLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I couldn’t help myself.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Only now does Tom realise the voice isn’t in his head. He looks across the room at Mr. Kepler.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Mr. KEPLER (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It was the Black Knight. I went to bed with Mrs. Kepler. I woke up. There was meat in my mouth. Human flesh, all salty and sour.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>A sudden rage grips Tom. Screaming, he launches himself at Mr. Kepler. Drives his fist into the old man’s face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Mr. Kepler does not resist. Sits there passively as Tom lays into him again and again. There is even a smile on his face when Tom throttles him. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom continues to grip Mr. Kepler’s throat for some seconds after the old man has expired. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>When he finally lets go, he crawls on his knees to the side of the bed and strokes Barbara’s hair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It wasn’t me, Barbara. It was old Mr. Kepler. There was nothing I could do. You understand, don’t you, Barbara?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Here, I’ll tell you what? How about you and me going downstairs and watching the Great British Shopping Experience? We can use my company credit card. Let’s get that cruet set you wanted.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And maybe some Harry Potter slippers. Remember, you were thinking about getting them but thought it might be a bit childish? Well, bollocks to that. If you want Harry Potter slippers, then Harry Potter slippers you shall have.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom stands. Gently lifts Barbara from the bed. Carries her to the door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="44" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 2/8" Page="57" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="YOUTUBE VOICEOVER"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. Tom’s office - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom is watching a government-sponsored video on </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">YouTube</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Youtube VOICEOVER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Under no circumstances must you go outside, not even to bury a corpse.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If you have a corpse in your home or other secure place, put it in a body bag or wrap it securely in several layers of sheets, curtains, canvas and whatever other material comes to hand. Bind this covering with any of the following:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Parcel tape</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Duct tape</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wiring (e.g. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">computer</Text>
      <Text> power cable)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>String</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Rope</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Twine</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Etc…</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If you have a freezer large enough to accommodate the corpse, place it in there. Otherwise store the corpse in a dry, dark place much as you would if it was food.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thoroughly sanitise all areas and items that have been in contact with the corpse.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Always wash your hands after handling cadavers.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do not leave the corpse outside, whether in your garden or out in the road.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Keep dead bodies away from children and pets.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>For other tips on dealing with a corpse inside your home, look in the comments section below. And if you found this video interesting, smash that like button!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom sets about wrapping Mr. Kepler’s body as per the instructions above. As he does so, he seems strangely content.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He wraps Mr. Kepler in bed sheets and curtains then binds him with parcel tape.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>When he is done -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And here’s one I prepared earlier!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom picks up Mr. Kepler and throws him over his shoulder. He goes out to -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="45" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="58" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Landing - day - conTINUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>- then downstairs to -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="46" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="58" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Hallway - day - contiNUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>- and into -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="47" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="58" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. LiVING ROOM - DAY - continuous</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara has been propped up on the settee. She is ‘watching’ a public information film regarding the Black Knight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom looks around for somewhere to put Mr. Kepler. Eventually puts him in the corner. He then sits next to Barbara.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s this then? More government propaganda? They must think we’re right mugs. Why don’t they put on something cheerful like Tom and Jerry cartoons? Or Lady and the Tramp? God, I love that film. You know that bit where they’re eating spaghetti?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom mutes the television.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara topples against Tom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom gently takes hold of Barbara and manoeuvres her into an upright position and places her elbow on the arm of the settee.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Things are going to be a lot easier once rigor mortis sets in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Did I tell you Mr. Kepler called today? I was right you know - about him being dead, only he wasn't dead when I said it but he is dead now. So now we won't have to put up with Bach at 6 in the morning any more. Every cloud and all that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now let's look at this face of yours.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom inspects Barbara’s ruined face, touching it delicately with his finger tips.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You never did look your best first thing in the morning, did you? Now let’s see what I can do.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>From the sideboard, Tom fetches Barbara’s sewing kit. He takes out the scissors from it and trims away ragged bits of flesh and hanging skin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s better but we’re not there yet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="48" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2" Page="59" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRODY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. liviNG ROOM - DAY - later</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom brings in a washing up bowl full of papier-mache which he lays at Barbara’s feet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He lovingly applies the papier-mache to Barbara’s face. Filling in the holes. Building her a new cheek, new lips.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Enjoying himself.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>As he works, he chats to Barbara.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know when I was in the office last week - or was it the week before? - I heard a really funny joke. It was about a policeman and a frog and damned if I can remember it. The punch line's something about a camel. Made me laugh like a drain.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If only I could remember it. Tell you what: I'll look it up on the Internet - assuming the Internet's still a thing, which it was last time I checked.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now hold still or I'm likely to cut you and we don't want that, do we?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why am I so terrible at remembering jokes? Some people seem to have an endless supply of them but not me. I'm pretty much a joke free zone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>When he is done, Barbara looks a lot like her old self</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You've got something on your chin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom takes out his handkerchief and spits on it. He dabs at Barbara’s chin until all the blood is gone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>There now. That's better. As soon as your face has dried out, we’ll slap on some make-up and you’ll be looking as beautiful as ever.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom sits down and puts the sound up on the television.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Dan Brody is on the Great British Shopping Experience.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BroDY (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, I don't know about anyone else, but I for one am getting heartily fed up with all the government propaganda films messing up my broadcasting schedule.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>OK - there's a zombie apocalypse. We get it! Now can we all just get on with our flipping lives, thank you very much?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And that’s all I need - my producer bleating in my ear. Apparently we can't say the word “zombie” because it's politically incorrect. Yes, Sandra, I know they're not zombies in the literal sense because they're not actually dead. So what do you want me to call them? Flesh-eating maniacs? Will flesh-eating maniacs do you? How about alternative carnivores?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Can I at least use the word apocalypse?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Because, Sandra, it is a fucking apocalypse, you dozy cow!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And now she's gone to the ladies to cry her eyes out - again! Oh boo </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">hoo</Text>
      <Text> </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">hoo</Text>
      <Text>. Very mature, Sandra. Very mature! No wonder the BBC turned you </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>down!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>OK so where was I before I was so rudely interrupted? Oh yes - silk underwear. Now who doesn't like silk underwear - especially when it's this flimsy?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara’s head lolls to one side. Her ear drops onto Tom’s lap.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom picks up the ear.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now where did I put the super glue?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BRODY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Between you and me, ladies and gentlemen, I’m wearing a pair of these lovely panties right now and I’ve never been happier.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="49" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="61" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. LivING ROOM - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom and Barbara are watching “It’s A Wonderful Life” on television. It’s the part where Jimmy Stewart’s character, George Bailey, bursts into the entrance hall crying ‘Mary’ and finds himself confronted </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">by,a</Text>
      <Text> newspaper reporter a sheriff and Carter the bank examiner.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>As the soppiness builds, Tom wipes a tear from his eye.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>A JET ROARS by overhead.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom puts a loving arm around Barbara.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The television screen suddenly goes blank.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh what the hell! It was almost finished!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The television starts to BLEEP.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BLEEP... BLEEP... BLEEP...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No! Not now! Too early! I’m not ready.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BLEEP...! BLEEP...! BLEEP...!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BLEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEP!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The room fills with green light.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom convulses. Starts to scream.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Right" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="5.50" RightIndent="7.10" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Transition">
      <Text>BLACKOUT:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="62" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Living room - NIGHT - LATER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Right" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="5.50" RightIndent="7.10" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Transition">
      <Text>Fade in:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>On the television: </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Center" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Bold">THE GREAT BRITISH SHOPPING EXPERIENCE IS OFF THE AIR
WE'LL BE BACK SOON</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom wakes. He spends a few moments taking stock of himself.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He looks at Barbara and can no longer deny the reality of her death.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sic transit </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">gloria</Text>
      <Text> </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">mundi</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom kisses Barbara on the forehead.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He fetches her make-up bag and touches up her face for her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="51" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 2/8" Page="62" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANNOUNCER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CAVELL"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Living room - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom is on the settee next to Barbara. Eating baked beans straight from the can.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>On the television: </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Bold">NORMAL SERVICE WILL BE RESUMED AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The screen goes blank.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Announcer (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>There now follows an announcement from the Right Honourable Arthur Cavell, Prime Minister of the United Kingdom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom flicks a spoonful of baked beans at the screen.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Wanker</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Television cuts to the Prime Minister’s office.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Cavell is sat behind a desk looking at camera.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>CAVEll (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>My fellow citizens, these are without doubt the darkest days our nation has ever faced. We are in the midst of an emergency so dire I was left with no choice but to declare martial law - to effectively turn these hallowed isles, this bastion of democracy, into a police state.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It was not an easy decision to make, nor one I made lightly, and I am truly sorry for the pain it has caused so many of you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Unfortunately, since the imposition of martial law, things have gotten worse, not better. The horrendous effects of the so-called Black Knight satellite coupled with mass desertion within the armed forces has rendered martial law ineffective as a means of keeping order. Therefore, I hereby decree that it is at an end. You may leave the safety of your houses if you so wish.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>To put it bluntly, it is now every man for himself. Do whatever you must in order to survive.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Good luck and may God preserve us all.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Fuck off.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The screen goes blank. Stays blank.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom flicks through channel after channel. All are blank.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="52" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 3/8" Page="63" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MCGREW"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WARBURG"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Tom’s office - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom is at his PC. On </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">YouTube</Text>
      <Text>, he does a search for ‘Black Knight’, which returns hundreds of thousands of videos to choose from.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He spots a video by Martin MCGREW.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>OK, Martin 'Daddy was a Martian' McGrew. Let's hear what you've got to say.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom clicks on the video in question.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>McGrew speaks to camera from his bedroom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>MCGREW (ON PC)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hi and welcome to the latest podcast from The Church of Divine Retribution. I’m the Reverend Martin McGrew and I speak Venusian.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>For years now, I and my flock have suffered ridicule and derision from those who choose to not believe. When I said I had been chosen by the Elders of Venus to spread the One True Gospel to the people of Earth, I was laughed at. My children disowned me and my wife tried to have me put away in a lunatic asylum. And where are they now? Dead. All dead.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And millions of unbelievers have died along with them, and in the days to come, millions more will die also. As it is written in the Book of </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Karketh</Text>
      <Text> the Divine Astronaut so it is and so it shall be.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>There is no path to salvation except through Borganesh, the Great Cosmic Messiah who laid to waste the cities of Mars because the Martians would not listen. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>As foretold in the Analects of Xileg the Buffoon, after sleeping for more than one million years in the heart of the sun, Borganesh has returned and he is not happy!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>He has seen the evil that has unfolded on this once-fair planets. He has gazed in horror upon the blackness that fills the heart of men. And he has said, ‘Enough is enough! This cannot go on.’</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Not too long ago, Borganesh came to me in a dream. ‘Martin,’ he said, ‘blessed are thou and thy flock for thine eyes are open and your heart is pure. Thee and thee alone have proven worthy of my love.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>‘As to the rest of your accursed race, death to them all! Death, I say! Death!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>‘I shall send forth the agent of my vengeance - Karpark the Destroyer, who shall be known as the Black Knight. All shall perish except for congregation of The Church of Divine Retribution and a handful of comely maidens.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>‘As for thyself, Martin McGrew, you must choose for yourself one dozen of the comeliest, most fertile members of the fairer sex with whom to begin again the race of Man.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>‘Yes, thou shalt have 12 mates, each fairer than any other on thine planet. And ye shall bless them with thy seed and they shall bless you with progeny.’</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And then Borganesh was gone and I awoke with a vigour I had not known since the days of my youth. Hear me women of Earth: though none are worthy of the honour, I must obey my Lord and take into my care one dozen of you for the purposes of procreation.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If you are of good breeding stock and you wish to survive the apocalypse, send me pictures of yourself - lots of pictures as explicit and lewd as you know how. Make me beat my meat and you shall walk among the chosen!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>OOS: Detective Inspector WARBURG is KNOCKING on the front door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom is irritated. Ignores the KNOCKING.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>It continues.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WarburG (O.S.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mr. Caxton! Open up! This is the police. Open up or I will break down your door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>KNOCK! KNOCK! KNOCK!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG (O.S.) (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mr. Caxton! You are not in any trouble but if you do not open this door I will have no choice but to arrest you!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>KNOCK! KNOCK! KNOCK!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(shouting)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>All right! I'm bloody coming! Keep your fucking hair on!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Harassed, Tom goes down to -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="53" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="66" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WARBURG"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. HALLWAY - DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>KNOCK! KNOCK! KNOCK!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The front door is full of bullet holes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WaRBURG (O.S.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mr. Caxton! This is your last warning! Open up or else!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>KNOCK! KNOCK! KNOCK!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ToM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>For Chrissakes! Give it a rest!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom drags the table away from the door. Unchains and opens the door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>About time.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Warburg flashes his warrant card, puts it straight back in his pocket.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mr. Caxton? Mr. Tom Caxton?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Detective Inspector Warburg. Mind if I come in?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The house is a mess.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Right now, every house is a mess, Mr. Caxton. Every street. Every town, city and village.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If I spot your Y-fronts peeking out from under a chair, I promise not to faint.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Warburg takes Tom's silence as an invitation and steps over the threshold. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WaRBURG (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That the living room there, is it?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Warburg pushes open the living room door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>A cup of tea would be nice.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom follows Warburg into -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="54" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6 2/8" Page="67" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WARBURG"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. LivING ROOM - DAY - coNTINUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No water. No gas. And pretty soon I expect we’ll have no electricity.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WaRBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh well. Never mind.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Warburg spots Barbara’s corpse on the settee but says nothing about it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Take a seat, will you, Mr. Caxton?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom sits next to Barbara.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Warburg nods in the direction of Mr. Kepler.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I see you have a corpse, Mr. Caxton. I must commend you on how well you’ve wrapped him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>My neighbour.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Did you kill him?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I throttled him to death. Are you going to arrest me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>To what end, Mr. Caxton?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It wasn’t the Black Knight. I deliberately and quite consciously killed him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I'm sure you had your reasons and I'm not here to judge you. I'm here to find out about the man who was shot on your doorstep: a Mr. Josef K. Did you know him?'</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Then can you explain why he came to your house when there was a curfew on?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>There were soldiers chasing after him. I think he just made a beeline for the nearest house.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Any port in a storm, hey? I suppose that makes sense.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Warburg takes out his note pad and pencil. He wets the tip of the pencil with his tongue.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WaRBURG (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tell me what happened.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I really didn't see anything. I was sitting at the table over there playing Cluedo with my wife.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>When you say your wife, I presume you mean the lady sitting next to you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes. Barbara, this is Detective Inspector Warburg. Detective Inspector Warburg - Barbara.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Delighted to meet you, Mrs. Caxton.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She's the reason I killed Mr. Kepler. He ate half her face. I don't know if you can tell.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It's not immediately obvious.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I used papier-mâché to fill in the missing bits.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ingenious. You've done a very good job.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thank you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now, these soldiers - did they give any warnings before they shot Mr. K?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I heard one of them shout “Stop or we'll shoot”.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(writing in his note pad)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>“Stop or we’ll shoot.”</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>He shouted it twice.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And did Mr. K stop?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No. He came running up to my front door. Banged on it. Begged to be let in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thereby disobeying a lawful order! I see. And I take it, judging from the state of the front door, that he was right on your doorstep when they shot him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I couldn’t help him, Inspector.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nor should you have tried. By deliberately breaking the curfew, Josef K. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">signed</Text>
      <Text> his own death warrant. If you’d interfered, you’d be dead too.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Warburg puts away his notebook and pencil.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, you’ve told me all I need to know. Thank you for your cooperation, Mr. Caxton.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>When I get back to the station, I'll have the desk sergeant post you a compensation form. There's no reason for the army not to reimburse you for your door. They could have dragged Mr. K out into the street and shot him there. But that’s the military for you - no respect for property.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Incidentally, Mr. Caxton, you do know your wife is dead, don't you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ve been meaning to wrap her up like they sign on those public information films, but I haven’t gotten around to it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Can’t quite bring yourself to say goodbye, I suppose. Perfectly understandable.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you mind if I take a closer look?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Be my guest.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Warburg kneels before Barbara and takes her hand in his. He flexes her finger.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m impressed, Mr. Caxton. You’re not a mortician by any chance?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No. I’m a commercial artist.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Perhaps you should consider a career change. Morticians are in demand right now. There’s quite a backlog of stiffs to get through.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Warburg stands and leans forward. He looks like he is about to kiss Barbara. Instead, he sniffs her cheek.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WaRBURG (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Have you noticed that the dead smell different now?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I've not had the opportunity to sniff that many corpses.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, that's the thing about my job, Mr. Caxton. I've seen them dredged out of canals, hanging from trees, lying in the smouldering ashes of burnt-out buildings looking like massive chunks of charcoal, wedged in drains, laid out on mortuary slabs etc, etc.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s funny, isn’t it? There’s only one way into this world but a million ways to leave it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>To my mind every corpse is different to every other corpse except in one respect - the smell, Mr. Caxton. All corpses smell the same - except since the Black Knight the smell is different. It's richer. Spicier. More - and I hesitate to use this word, Mr. Caxton, but it's the only one that fits - sexier!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You wouldn’t think - would you? - that there could be anything sexy about a corpse, and yet...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It's that green light the Black Knight pumps out. Some people say it's orgone energy - the very essence of life - and I think they’re right: the Black Knight is killing us with life.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You've got to admit, Mr. Caxton, that since the Black Knight started doing the rounds, you've felt more alive than ever.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I suppose I have.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And randier! Like you're on steroids. Personally, I only have to see a woman and I'm rock hard. And here’s the funny thing. It’s the dead ones that turn me on the most. There’s nothing makes me stiff quite as much as a stiff - if you know what I mean.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I think you’d best leave, Inspector.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>My wife died during the first transit. I woke up to find my hands around her throat and her tongue in the back of my throat. Gave me quite a shock, that did. Then I realised I had a boner that could have taken someone’s eye out. And with my wife still warm... Well, you’re a man of the world, Mr. Caxton. I don’t have to tell you what happened next.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Bloody hell, man! You’re sick.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I keep my wife’s </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">csdaver</Text>
      <Text> in the freezer. Treat me nice and I’ll thaw her out for you. Of course, I’d expect a bit of quid pro quo, if you know what I mean.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Would you be interested in a foursome, Mr. Caxton?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Get away from my wife!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom jumps up. Drags Warburg away from Barbara.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Warburg seems to find it funny.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Enraged, Tom kicks Warburg in the face. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Warburg lands on his back. Tom dives on top of his.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The two men tussle.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s it, Mr. Caxton. Release all that sexual tension. Beat me to a pulp then rape me!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom rabbit punches Warburg in the kidneys. Punches him in the face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Warburg dislodges Tom. Manoeuvres him onto his back. Straddles Tom. Punches him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>In desperation, Tom grabs at Warburg’s crotch, aiming for his scrotum but grabbing his erect penis instead.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now you’re talking.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom twists Warburg’s penis, throwing him off-balance. Sits up suddenly.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Warburg lands up on his back again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom wraps his hands around Warburg’s throat. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(gasping)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s it. Squeeze harder now... Harder!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom squeezes harder. It is not enough for him. So he leans down and bites Warburg’s ear. Comes up with the ear in his mouth.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He spits the ear in Warburg’s face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Warburg couldn’t be happier.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom continues to throttle Warburg.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>WARBURG (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sweet Jesus! I’m coming.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Disgusted, Tom lets go of Warburg’s throat. Jumps to his feet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The realisation that he’s just killed the policeman excites him. He turns to his wife, hands on hips, chest thrust out, basking in her (imaginary) adoration.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>His hands strays to the front of his trousers.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He all but throws himself at Barbara. Kisses her ruined mouth. Runs a hand up her leg.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="55" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="73" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRODY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. LIVING ROOM - DAY - LATER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom is sitting on the floor, his back against the wall. Crying. Looking apologetically at Barbara.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Miserable, defeated, Tom gets up and drags Detective Inspector Warburg’s lifeless body across the room and dumps it next to Mr. Kepler.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Then he slopes off out of the room, returning shortly with a bottle of whisky.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He sits down next to Barbara. Turns on the television.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>On comes Dan Brody and the Great British Shopping Channel.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ToM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Look, dear. Your favourite presenter.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom starts on the whisky, drinking straight from the bottle.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BRODY (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, what can I say, ladies and gentlemen? If I didn't see it with my own two eyes, I just would not believe it! Less than twenty quid for a pair of cushions fit for a king.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I tell you, if His Majesty himself parked his arse on one of these he'd be ruined for other cushions for life. Let's get a close up - can we, Henry? - so our wonderful viewers can feast their eyes on the glory of this stitching. You see that? You wouldn’t find better stitching on a Gucci bag. And this silky finish - hmmm so smooth, so sexy. I tell you, folks, this cushion is so sensuous I’d happily fuck it! In fact, as soon as my shift is over, I’m off to the stock room to have me a cushion gang bang!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="56" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="74" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRODY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Living room - morning</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom, empty whisky bottle at his feet, wakes up on the settee with a massive hangover.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>On the television: Dan Brody and the GBSE channel.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BRODY (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(filled with despair)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>They're coming back! It's not over. It will never be over.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom gropes around for the remote control and fails to find it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He closes his eyes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BrODY  (ON TV)(CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We thought it was as bad as it could get but we were wrong. The situation is worse than ever! Dear God, when will this nightmare end? It won’t will it? It will never end!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I didn’t believe in the devil because I didn’t believe in God. Now, I still don’t believe in God but I do believe in the devil! People, there is evil afoot. Trust no-one, not even the dead. Especially not the dead! </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If you see a corpse, burn it! Do you hear me? BURN IT!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The dead are coming back. Oh God, they’re coming back!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom’s hand closes around the remote. He turns off the television.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Relieved to be no longer having to listen to the ranting of Dan Brody, he opens his eyes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Seconds later, he throws up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="57" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="75" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. BEDROOM - DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom strips to his underwear. Washes himself as best he can with bottles of mineral water, heedless of the carpet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He finds clean clothes. Gets dressed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="58" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="75" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Kitchen - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom opens a tin of stewing steak. Eats it directly from the can.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="59" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="75" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. HallWAY - DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom drags Warburg’s body up the stairs.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Onto -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="60" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="75" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Landing - day - continuous</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>- and then into -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="61" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="75" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Tom’S OFFICE - day - continUOUS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom dumps Warburg’s body on the floor. He rushes out. Returns shortly with a tee shirt, a leather jacket, Barbara’s make-up bag and a chainsaw. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Standing over Warburg, Tom starts the chainsaw. Gleefully waves it around. Brings it towards Warburg as if he is about to cut through him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom kills the chainsaw. Kisses it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He then removes Warburg’s upper clothing and replaces it with the tee shirt and jacket.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>When Warburg is dressed again, Tom manoeuvres him onto the leather chair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom seems very happy as he sets about transforming Warburg’s face into that of Butcher Baby.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>When he is done, he equips Warburg with the chainsaw then uses his phone to photograph “Butcher Baby”.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom transfers the photos to his PC and uses them to dummy up some promo posters.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="62" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="76" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. LiviNG ROOM - DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom enters carrying a copy of “The Call of the Wild” by Jack London.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He sits next to Barbara.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>My favourite book - “Call of the Wild” by Jack London. I keep threatening to read it to you and there’s no time like the present.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Between you and me, I need something to do. Nobody warned me the end of the world would be this boring.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom opens “Call of the Wild” and begins to read it out loud.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(reading)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Chapter 1. Into the primitive.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Buck did not read the newspapers, or he would have known that trouble was brewing, not alone for himself, but for every tide-water dog, strong of muscle and with warm, long hair, from Puget Sound to San Diego. Because men, groping in the Arctic darkness, had found a yellow metal, and because steamship and transportation companies were booming the find, thousands of men were rushing into the Northland. These men wanted dogs, and the dogs they wanted were heavy dogs, with strong muscles by which to toil, and furry coats to protect them from the frost.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="63" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3 3/8" Page="76" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BATES"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BBC ANNOUNCER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="FISCHER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="GROUND CONTROL"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ISABELLE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="PENROSE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RECORDED MESSAGE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Living room - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Sat next to Barbara, Tom is watching BBC News which is showing a shot inside an Apollo module with a caption: </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Bold">LIVE from inside the White Knight Mission Capsule.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Louise Bates again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Bates (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Until this moment, Neil Armstrong was undoubtedly the world's most famous astronaut, but surely from here on in, the names of these two brave men - Jurgen Fischer and Walter Penrose - will eclipse even that of the first man on the moon.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The picture you are seeing comes from a hand-held camera inside an Apollo command and service module which is more or less above the terminator - that is to say the division between night and day. On the night side, towards where the module is heading, you can see much of the Middle East bathed in green light, the significance of which can be lost on no-one.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It makes one sick to think of the mayhem underway wherever the green light seeds its evil - the madness and the murder, the cold, calculated genocide perpetrated by an alien civilisation that for all any of us knows may no longer even exist.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Bates falls silent, her commentary giving way to radio chatter between Ground Control and the two astronauts, FISCHER and PENROSE.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Penrose (ON TV) </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Houston, we're all set to go here. The White Knight is primed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>
BEEP.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>GROUND CONTROL (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Roger that, Walter.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BEEP.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>PenROSE (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I have a visual sighting of the Black Knight. It's hard to make out because it really is black. About the only thing I can say about it is that it's quite irregular in shape and it looks... well, it looks evil.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BEEP.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Ground control (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Roger that, Walter.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Jurgen, is there any chance you can get it on camera for us?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BEEP.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Fischer (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Roger, Houston.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BEEP.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>For a few seconds, as the camera is swung about, the picture goes mental, becoming a fleeting segue of nonsensical images before settling down into a view from the front of the capsule.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>In the midst of the blackness of space can be seen something even blacker, only discernible because it is blocking out the stars behind it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>This is the Black Knight satellite.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Bates (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And there we have it! The first close-up image of the Black Knight satellite! What a moment this is!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The command module drifts ever closer to the satellite with each moment bringing with it slightly more detail. As the alien craft fills the screen, it is possible to make out what looks like portholes with sheets of black metal filling in for glass. All sorts of box-shaped artefacts protrude from its main shell, giving the impression of an agglomeration of spare parts rescued from a scrap yard and randomly thrown together.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>PenROSE (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Houston, I can see many dents in the hull of that thing. I'm guessing they were made by meteors but who knows? Maybe the Black Knight once came under attack?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BEEP.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>GROUND CONTROL (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Roger that, Walter.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BEEP.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>PENROSE (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We are applying </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">retros</Text>
      <Text> to maintain our distance. This is as near as the command module goes. Requesting permission to commence the next phase of our mission, Houston.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BEEP.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>GROUND CONTROL (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Permission is granted. Proceed at your own pace and God bless and God speed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>
Something resembling a domestic fridge floats into view.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Bates (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And that, ladies and gentlemen, is what NASA is calling the White Knight, for obvious reasons. Without further details, we can only assume it to be an atomic weapon of some sort. The two astronauts are steering it towards the Black Knight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is far closer than any earthly weapon has ever been to the deadly satellite. Come to that, no man has ever been as close to it as these two brave astronauts whose lives are very much on the line right now.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The plan seems to be to somehow attach the White Knight to the Black Knight and detonate it at what amounts to point blank range guaranteeing total annihilation of this hideous artefact.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Dear god, dare we believe that our salvation is unfolding right before our very eyes? Is this the end of the nightmare?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We know not from whence the Black Knight came, nor who sent it or why. What we do know is - </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>White light suddenly bursts forth on the television screen and dies abruptly. The screen is now blank.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>A few moments of indecipherable background chatter gives way to the voice of Louise Bates.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Bates (ON TV) (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ladies and gentlemen, it seems that the White Knight - whatever it is or rather was - has detonated prematurely. Thankfully, it went off within a hundred or so metres of its target which must surely mean the end of the Black Knight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sadly, however, two brave astronauts - Jurgen Fischer and Walter Penrose - have sacrificed their lives to save humanity and in doing so have written their names large across the sky and joined the pantheon of immortal heroes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>
Tom laughs at Bates’ cornball phraseology.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="64" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="80" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BBC ANNOUNCER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ISABELLE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RECORDED MESSAGE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Kitchen - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>From the cupboard under the sink, he digs out a box of ant poison. Reads the bumf on the box.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(reading)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Destroys ants without mercy. Guaranteed 100% effective. Warning: not for human consumption. Ingestion may cause death.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom takes the box out to - </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="65" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="80" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. Garden - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom stands contemplating the Milky Way for a while, perhaps seeking signs of the supposedly destroyed Black Knight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He then turns on the porch light and kneels down in front of the ants nest.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Opens the box and prepares to pour its contents onto the nest.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom finds he can’t do it. The ants have done him no harm. What right has he to rain destruction down upon them?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Reconciled, he goes back indoors.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="66" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="80" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BATES"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ISABELLE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RECORDED MESSAGE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Living room - later</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom, on the settee, swigs whisky. On the television - Louise Bates has radiates despair and defeat.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Bates (ON TV) </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ladies and gentlemen, we have just received the worst news possible. The Black Knight has not been destroyed. Repeat: the Black Knight has not been destroyed. It is still functioning.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The White Knight mission has failed. This is the end. Truly the fucking end of everything. All I can do now is advise you all to do what I intend to do - find a painless way out of this shithouse of a world as soon as possible.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Goodbye and God bless.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="67" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="81" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Kitchen - nIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom takes a glass. Pours a large amount of ant poison into it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Goes to fill the glass with water. Of course, there is no water.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He searches the food cupboard and comes upon a bottle of lemonade.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He fills the glass with lemonade. Stirs the mixture and places the glass on the table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Then, with a scrubbing brush and what’s left of the lemonade, he removes the growth marks on the pantry door jamb.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Goes to -</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="68" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4 1/8" Page="81" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ISABELLE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RECORDED MESSAGE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOM"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. LiviNG ROOM - day - continuous</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom sits on the settee next to Barbara’s corpse.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Battling against his gag reflex, he downs the ant poison and somehow manages to keep it down.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He lies on his side and waits for the end.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>His phone rings. He answers it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tom Caxton.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">RECORDED MESSAGE (ON PHONE)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Congratulations! As a mobile phone owner you have been automatically entered into the National Smart Phone Lottery sponsored by Apple Computers in order to promote the use of smart phones. And guess what? You are this week's lucky winner of one million dollars. Yes, that's right: one million dollars. To claim your prize - </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom kills the call. Tosses aside the phone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The phone rings again. He retrieves it from where he dropped it and answers.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tom Caxton.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">ISABELLE (ON PHONE) </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh, Mr. Caxton! Thank God! I hope you don't mind me calling like this, only I've been every number on my own phone and nobody's answering. I think everybody's dead except for you and me, Mr. Caxton.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We could be the last people on Earth, which I suppose is one for the history books, only there won't be any more history books because history is finished. It’s over.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The reason I'm calling you, Mr. Caxton is that I'm dying.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh my God! Now that I’ve said it, it’s suddenly become real. I am dying! This is it. My life is over.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sixty sleeping pills. Little red things that look like sweets. Mother’s little helpers, I think they call them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I took them one at a time and after each one, I said a Hail Mary.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I can feel them working - slowing down my heartbeat, slowing down my brain, shutting down my vital organs. It’s a nice feeling in a way but scary and I don’t want to die alone, Mr. Caxton, which is why I got on the phone like they tell you to do in the advert. You know the one I mean? Where you have all those lonely people phoning each other and suddenly they're not lonely any more and the sun comes out and the clouds just disappear?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you a Catholic, Mr. Caxton? No, you're not. I remember that arsehole of a husband of mine saying you'd joined an atheist society, which - if you don't mind me saying so - is a very strange thing to do. Having a club for people who don't believe in God is like having a club for people who don't believe in the tooth fairy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The thing is, Mr. Caxton, I am a lifelong Catholic. Not a very devout one perhaps but I do confess my sins once in a while and here I am, committing the worst sin of all - suicide - and there's no priest around to grant me absolution.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What little time I have left, I want to use squaring things with my god. I think I’m a good person, Mr. Caxton, and I think God thinks so too but I crave his forgiveness. I really do.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you mind hearing my confession, Mr. Caxton? I know you're not a priest but that doesn't matter. It won’t be you I’m talking to. It will be God.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I think you should know, Mrs. Lynton, I'm dying too. I've ingested ant poison.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ISABELLE (ON PHONE)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Then as soon as I’ve confessed my sins, you should confess yours. Otherwise you're going to burn in Hell.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don't believe in God and I don't believe in Hell.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ISABELLE (ON PHONE)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Then I'm truly sorry because for you there is no salvation, no redemption.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Tom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Give me your confession, Mrs. Lynton.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ISABELLE (ON PHONE)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If I do, will you give me yours?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sure. Why not?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ISABELLE (ON PHONE) </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I think I should begin with my worst sin. No - I've already told you that. Then let's start with my second worst sin, Mr. Caxton.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What do they call it when someone kills their children? I know killing your brother is fratricide and killing your mum is matricide but what is it when it's your children? Never mind. It doesn't matter. Murder is murder.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I killed my children, Mr. Caxton.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I gave them a warm bath and fed them fish finger sandwiches washed down with Dr. Pepper laced with heroin. Did I tell you I'm a heroin addict, Mr. Caxton? That’s another sin to add to the list.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Beth and Peter went to sleep in each other's arms. They were happy because they were loved and they'd just had fish finger sandwiches. Then the Lord in his infinite mercy took their souls up to Paradise.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh, and one more sin while I think of it. I rejoiced at my husband losing his penis. I took pleasure in his pain.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Other than that, I have used the Lord's name in vain and I have committed the following sins: lust, greed, envy, pride and wrath. And I think that's about it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And now it's your turn, Mr. Caxton. Confess your sins before it’s too late.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t know how, Mrs. Lynton.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ISABELLE (ON PHONE)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Imagine you’re standing before God. What do you want say to him?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I want to say, “God, you blew it”.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom convulses. Drops his phone. Clutches his stomach.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Cries out in agony.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>ISABELLE (ON PHONE)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mr. Caxton? Are you OK?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom is in his death throes. He screams and kicks and tears at his hair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>IsABELLE  (ON PHONE) (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Jesus loves you, Tom Caxton. He knows you’re a good man.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m praying, Mr. Caxton. I’m praying for both of us.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom pays no attention to Isabelle. He is too busy dying to care.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>IsABELLE (ON PHONE) (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(singing)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">Jesus loves me, this I know / for the Bible tells me so / Little ones to him belong; / they are weak but he is strong.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">Yes, Jesus loves me! / Yes, Jesus loves me! / Yes, Jesus loves me! / The Bible tells me so.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The pain intensifies.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh God, oh God! Make it stop! Make it stop!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Isabelle sings on, growing ever quieter as her life slips away.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom crawls on the floor. Writhes. Sweats. Screams.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>TOM (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Barbara!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Eventually, he dies.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="69" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="85" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. HALLWAY - night - continuous</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Through the letter box comes an avalanche of packages. Each bears the logo of the Great British Shopping Experience.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" Number="70" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="22" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2" Page="85" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRODY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. living room - night - continuous</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom and Barbara are lying dead on the floor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>In the corner sit the corpses of Mr. Kepler (wrapped in sheets) and Detective Inspector Warburg.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The television switches to the Great British Shopping Experience Channel.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Dan Brody faces the camera with a jerrycan at his feet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>Brody (ON TV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is the final testament of Daniel Reinhart Brody, star of stage and television.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>By the time you view this - assuming there's anyone left to do so - I will be dead. More than dead: I will be ashes. My body will be gone for good. The Black Knight shall not have it!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>People, heed my warning. Do not bury the dead. Destroy them utterly or they will come back.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>They will come back!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Maybe, one day, there will be an end to this nightmare. Maybe they'll find a way to destroy the Black Knight. Maybe it will just switch itself off. Maybe some remnant of humanity will survive this catastrophe and start all over again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Maybe. Maybe. Maybe.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>But come the Day of Salvation, I for one will not be around to see it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Brody is the very picture of serenity as he picks up the jerrycan and douses himself in petrol.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>He takes out a lighter and thumbs the flint. As soon as he has a flame, he combusts with a loud WHOOMF!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Screaming and flailing his arms, Brody runs at the camera causing it to white out. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Screen goes blank for a few seconds. Then we are back to the start of Brody’s last testament.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="3.50" RightIndent="7.25" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Character">
      <Text>BRODY (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is the final testament of Daniel Reinhart Brody, star of stage and television.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>By the time you view this - assuming there's anyone left to do so - I will be dead. More than dead: I will be ashes. My body will be gone for good.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Screen goes blank. Sudden silence. Then...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>BLEEP…! BLEEP…! BLEEP…!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>The Black Knight approaches</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>As the BLEEPS merge one into the other, the room fills with green light.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Abruptly, the bleeps stop.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>In the corner, the package containing old Mr. Kepler twitches. Re-animated, the old man struggles to free himself.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Detective Inspector Warburg opens his eyes. Rises.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom opens his eyes just as Barbara opens her one good one. They stand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom and Warburg walk zombie-fashion towards each other. When the meet, they attempt to strangle each other. Fall to the floor. Wrestle, each attempting to eat the other.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara takes her knitting needles from their hiding place.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>She walks up to the fighting men, kneels and thrusts the needles into Warburg’s eyes, whereupon he ceases to struggle.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>There is an obscenely satisfying SLURP as Barbara pulls out Warburg’s eyeballs on her needles.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>She and Tom eat an eyeball each.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara bites into Warburg’s neck, ripping out his windpipe.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom goes for the detective’s belly and tears out chunks of flesh until intestines are exposed. Tom pulls out the intestines. Starts eating them from one end.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbara starts on the other end.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>Tom and Barbara, united in half-death, lovingly munch their way towards one another.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.50" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Action">
      <Text>FREEZE FRAME.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Right" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="5.50" RightIndent="7.10" SpaceBefore="11" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Transition">
      <Text>FINAL FADE OUT.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
  </Content>

  <Watermarking Text=""/>

